In a music group, there are different types of musical instruments. There are wind instruments, string instruments, and percussion instruments.

All instruments have as attributes their name and their price. Additionally, they have a method called play().
This method is abstract in the Instrument class and, therefore, must be implemented in the child classes.

If a wind instrument is being played, the method should display on the console: "A wind instrument is sounding"
If a string instrument is being played: "A string instrument is sounding"
And if a percussion instrument is being played: "A percussion instrument is sounding".

The process of loading a class only happens once.
Demonstrate that the loading can be triggered by the creation of the first instance of this class
or by accessing a static member of this class.

Research information about initialization blocks and static blocks in Java.

